Univariate Feature Analysis: 1-Year Survival

Author

R. Jerome Dixon

Published

July 29, 2025

Overview

This report presents a univariate analysis of the top features from a 1-year survival model. Each plot displays how the distribution of a feature varies by the binary outcome.

For the CatBoost partial dependence plots (PDPs), we visualize how the predicted probability changes as individual feature values vary, while holding all other features constant. These plots are based on raw, uncalibrated model predictions and are intended to reveal the marginal effect of each feature on the modelâs output.
